14. Bd2 a5 15. Qe1 Qd8 16. Bc3 e5
{ Solid and good enough for a draw - Black limits White's piece activity and forces him to act. }
17. Bxe5 Re8
{ The position inevitably simplifies - Black will win back the pawn with more trades incoming. }
18. f4 { White temporarily keeps the pawn but not for long. } 18... Qb6+ 19.
Bd4 Qb7 20. Bxf6 Bxe4 21. Qe2
{ White has no choice as keeping Black's light-squared bishop alive with  21.Bxg7  is too dangerous. }
21... gxf6 22. Qg4+ Kf8 23. Bxe4 Qxe4
{ Inevitably, the variation will end with something peaceful. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
