{ A bit of an awkward square for the queen, but Black is fighting against the Bf4 threat. }
13. d5
{ Practically quite understandable, but objectively it is still a mistake.   13.g3  Unfortunately for White, he can't improve the threat.  13...a6  14.Bf4  axb5!  15.Bxb8  Rxa1  16.Qxa1  Nc2+  Black wins a lot of material. }
13... exd5 14. cxd5 Bf5 15. Na3
{ Perez Pietronave, C. @@StartBracket@@2203@@EndBracket@@ - Iermito, S. @@StartBracket@@2463@@EndBracket@@ Buenos Aires Duchamp Memorial op 5th 2013. Black should have played a little more aggressively here. }
15... O-O 16. dxc6 Bf6 17. Be3 Rd8 18. Nd2 bxc6
{ White has incredible practical difficulties - not only will the queenside rook have to be traded for the bishop, but Black also has a strong initiative as well. }
