9. Qe2 Qxe2+ 10. Kxe2 Nd7 { White can't keep his extra pawn. } 11. d4
{ Here begins a forced variation. } 11... Bxd4 12. Nxd4 Bxg2 13. Rg1 Bh3
{ It's possible to look for adventures also here but if White is accurate, the position will end with a perpetual check. }
14. Nb5 Nxe5 { We imagine this to be a little shock to White! } 15. Nc7+ Kd7
16. Nxa8 Bg4+
{ Now White apparently can't avoid the perpetual check as  17.Ke3  would fuel Black's initiative with  17...Ne7  . }
17. Kf1 Bh3+ { Obviously, White is not interested in allowing a fork on f3. } *

