3... d5 4. e5
{ White could try offering to switch to the French Defense Advance variation. }
4... d4
{ There's no need to play the French Defense Advance variation, which could arise from  4...Nc6  5.d4  , but if you're a big fan, it's up to you! In the arising positions, both sides have their structural advantages, and often it depends if you can make 'the right trade' to leave the opponent without 'the attackers'.  With the last move, Black makes sure that White can't strengthen the center with the natural d4. }
5. Bd3
{ This awkward-looking move is the most popular move in the position - White continues development, intending to castle short. The bishop is often rerouted to e4 to target the black knight on c6  @@StartBracket@@assuming it's there@@EndBracket@@ and then to pressure the black pawn on d4. }
5... Bd7
{ The universal response against every setup that White chooses! Black brings out the light-squared bishop to c6, otherwise, that bishop may never see the daylight. }
6. O-O Bc6
{ Black positions the bishop on c6 and is waiting for White to define his setup. }
7. Re1
{ A general developing move, thinking about a future Be4 and lifting the rook on the 4th rank while not yet defining the setup at the queenside. }
7... g5
{ A typical trick at Black's disposal - since the White rook is already on e1, the white knight at the moment doesn't have a single retreat square from the ...g4 threat. Black is also thinking about ...Bg7 and perhaps also ...Nd7 to win the pawn on e5. }
8. b4
{ An interesting counter-offensive idea.   8.h3?  this only fuels Black's initiative  8...h5  . }
8... g4 9. b5 Bd5
{ Some complications are about to start but Black's chances look good. } 10. c4
Bxf3 11. gxf3 gxf3 12. Qxf3
{ This was played in Zhigalko, S. @@StartBracket@@2655@@EndBracket@@ - Ladva, O. @@StartBracket@@2401@@EndBracket@@ European Blitz championship Minsk 2015. Here Black could have played it out a little more aggressively. }
12... Nd7 13. Qxb7 Rb8
{ Black sacrifices a pawn to accelerate initiative - does it sound familiar? }
14. Qf3 Qg5+ 15. Qg3 Bh6
{ A very unusual resource - Black doesn't mind trading the queens but in the process, the e5-pawn will be lost. Once it's gone, Black's position should be preferred. }
