7... Ne7 8. cxd4 cxd4 9. Nc2 Nd7
{ By the way, it's possible to play  9...Ng6  and try to transpose to the previous sideline. This move might be a little more flexible if White doesn't take the pawn on d4 right away and tries to do something else. }
