{ Vysochin, S. @@StartBracket@@2560@@EndBracket@@ - Zubov, A. @@StartBracket@@2507@@EndBracket@@ Kiev Independence Cup-A 3rd 2003. The position is just equal and more pieces will be traded soon.   This is how the variation could continue:  19.Qf3  - in the game, White opted for 19.Qb3 and got a worse position as after capturing the dark-squared bishop, Black's d-pawn can march forward. Here, the black bishop is under attack.  19...Nxe5  20.Qxf5  Nc6  21.Nxd5  Nxd4  22.Qe4  Ne2+  . With this small trick, Black trades the knights as well.  23.Qxe2  Qxd5  and it looks like in the desert. }
