{ This transposes.   11...b4?  trying to close the queenside doesn't work.  12.Ne5!  Unfortunately for Black, this maneuver is possible as the g2 pawn is defended.  12...Nxe5  13.dxe5  White gets a lead in development and the position is opening - that's a bad combination, at least for Black.  13...Rd8  Mamedyarov, S. @@StartBracket@@2770@@EndBracket@@ - Vachier Lagrave, M. @@StartBracket@@2760@@EndBracket@@ FTX Crypto Cup Prelim 2021.  14.Bf3!  Qc7  15.Qe2  Bxf3  16.Qxf3  Black is balancing to be already lost. }
