{ The best practical chance for White is to try to sell back the pawn to finish the development and fight for the weakened light squares in the center. }
13... Nd4 14. Qd1
{ The knight can't be traded.  14.Nxd4?  White's position collapses due to a simple pin.  14...exd4  15.Ne4  Nxe4  16.dxe4  Rxf5!  Eventually, Black will be up something extra. }
14... h6
{ Black stops White's Bg5 idea for good and keeps control of the e4 and d5-squares. The pawn on f5 seemingly is not going anywhere, as in some scenarios like  15.Nh4  Black is also threatening to open the center with ...e4. }
15. Ne4 Nxf5 16. Bd2 Nxe4 17. dxe4 Nd4
