{ Of course, White wants to keep his light-squared bishop and the attacking chances at the kingside alive, but now comes the cold shower. }
18... Nxa2 { Black temporarily wins a pawn due to an unusual tactical trick. }
19. Kxa2 Bxd4 20. Qd3
{ Because of this counter-attack, White wins back the pawn.  20.Rxd4?  White can't take the bishop  20...Qa5+  . }
20... e5
{ It's important to guard the h3 square, otherwise White's Bxh7+ and Qh3 will end with a checkmate. }
21. Bxh7+ Kh8
{ Since Black is threatening to start a deadly queenside attack with ...Be6+ and ...Qa5 next, White must trade off the bishops. }
22. Bf5 Bxf5 23. Qxf5 exf4 { More simplifications are incoming. } 24. Qxf4 Qxf4
25. Bxf4 Bc5 { In the end we have an equal endgame. } *

