11. Ne4 Be7 12. Nxf6+
{ White might trade just the bishop and keep the knight on e4, but it doesn't change the evaluation of the position. }
12... Bxf6 13. Bxf6 Qxf6
{ Balogh, C. @@StartBracket@@2664@@EndBracket@@ - So, W. @@StartBracket@@2677@@EndBracket@@ Saint Louis SPICE Cup 6th 2012. The pawn on d4 is easy to defend and Black can target the c2-pawn as well. }
