6... Qc7 7. O-O Be7 8. d3
{ This seems to be necessary - after the impatient  8.d4  Black can play  8...cxd4  9.cxd4  exd4  10.Nxd4  and continue with the positional  10...Qe5  , forcing White to take on c6, giving Black an excellent position. }
8... O-O 9. Re1 Re8 { Black prepares to push ...d5. } 10. Qe2 h6 11. Nbd2 Bf8
12. h3
{ Zvjaginsev, V. @@StartBracket@@2663@@EndBracket@@ - Manukyan, S. @@StartBracket@@2272@@EndBracket@@ Russian Team Championship 2011. }
12... d5
{ This logical follow-up would get Black a better position after the opening. }
