{ With the White knight on b3 it would feel awkward to play  13...cxb4  and  --  14...d5  next as the White knight controls the c5 square. By the way, Black can already consider the ...cxb4 and ...d5 idea. }
14. d4
{ Objectively not good but it's not clear what White should do to prepare the d-pawn push. }
14... exd4 15. cxd4 cxb4
{ The unprotected bishop on b2 does not allow White to play d5. } 16. axb4 d5
{ Ansell, S. @@StartBracket@@2380@@EndBracket@@ - Nunn, J. @@StartBracket@@2600@@EndBracket@@ BCF-chT 9899 @@StartBracket@@4NCL@@EndBracket@@ 1998. White is in trouble as the pawn on b4 is very weak and his pieces are not well-positioned. }
