8. f4 Nf6
{ Black already is threatening with ...b4 to win the pawn on e4. White's  9.e5  here is not such an obvious choice at all as Black can respond in numerous ways, starting with  9...Bxg2  and ...Nd5 next, where thanks to White's included f4, the bishop on e3 is under attack. Also  9...b4  as the classical intermezzo move, or perhaps just  9...Nd5  should work just fine. }
