{ Black is treading carefully. } 18. Bb5+ Nd7
{ White's attack inevitably comes to an end - just a few more precise moves. }
19. Qe3 Qd4 20. Qg5 h6 21. Qf5 Ba6
{ Black is just in time to eliminate the dangerous pin. } 22. Rd1 Qe3+ 23. Kf1
Bxb5+ 24. Nxb5 Ra7 { The final nuance. } 25. Nxa7 Qxa7
{ Black's two minor pieces should dominate the rook and the two pawns if the queens remain on the board. White's king is also exposed. }
