13. Qd3
{ White controls the d4-square, but is now committed to positioning the queen to g3 first, before moving the bishop to d3. Big difference. }
13... O-O 14. Qg3 Bd4
{ A great move - Black stops White's plan before he manages to rearrange his position. At the moment the threat is to win the pawn on e4. }
15. Bd3 d5 { Start of a forced sequence. } 16. e5 Bxc3
{ Very important move order - Black needs to gain access to the e4-square for the knight. }
17. bxc3 Ne4 18. Bxe4 dxe4 19. f5
