10... Bd6
{ This must be quite an unexpected reply for White who should be expecting either ...Bxc3 or ...Be7. Black goes on the offensive. }
11. h3 c5
{ Black pushes away the White queen from the center, intending to continue with ...h6, ...Bd7 and castling long. }
12. Qd3
{ There are several queen retreat squares but they all look the same from Black's perspective, executing the same plan. }
12... h6 13. Bxf6
{ If the bishop goes to e3, Black can safely castle short and the white queen on d3 is feeling claustrophobic. If it goes to h4, White loses any access to f4 thrust, thus Black can play something active like 13...b5. }
13... gxf6 14. Rad1 Be7
{ Black's plan mostly is to castle long but there might be room for improvement. }
15. Bh5
{ White stops the incoming ...Bd7 due to the Bxf7 trick but now White also loses control of some of the queenside squares. }
15... c4 16. Qd4 Qc5
{ After the queen trade Black already wants to play ...Ke7 and start to activate the two bishops. }
