{ Black's idea is to find a good moment to push ...b4 and then ...d5. } 14. a3
{ Seems to be a necessary move. } 14... Qe5 15. f4 Qb8
{ The black queen here is quite active, preparing some pawn pushes and protecting the weakened dark squares on the queenside. }
16. f5
{ Going for the big attack is not such an obvious choice for White as he's missing pieces to conduct an attack and this maneuver weakens the e5-quare. }
16... Bxe3 17. Qxe3 f6 { The black knight is heading to e5. } *

