8... O-O
{ It's strange but this is quite a rare move order. Black wants to save time on ...Nbc6 and ...d6 so that it's possible to meet the Maroczy Bind with ...d5.   8...Nbc6  If Black includes this standard move here, there will be some practical problems with the d-pawn push.  9.Bxa7  Rxa7  10.c4  d5  Otherwise, you might never get a second chance.  11.exd5  exd5  12.cxd5  Qxd5  Black is forced to recapture with the queen and the Black rook in the open position feels weird on a7.  13.O-O  O-O  14.Nc3  Qe5  . Probably Black can hold this, but White is pushing. }
9. f4
{ A very tricky move order - White keeps the option of castling either way and, under the right circumstances, is ready to set up the Maroczy Bind again. }
9... Nbc6 10. Bxa7 { After  10.N1d2  we simply transpose to a later line. }
10... Rxa7 11. Nc3
{ White has no time for the Maroczy Bind since Black is ready to push ...d5. Once the white knight lands on c3, Black plays ...b5 for the typical counterplay ideas at the queenside. }
11... b5 12. O-O-O
{ The most challenging way to continue but now the game gets pretty sharp. }
12... b4 13. Na4 d6
{ Black's plan is simple - go after the stranded knight on a4. Check the following variations and see for yourself how difficult it can be for White to find the best moves. }
14. h4 { If White ignores Black's ideas, things can get messy very quickly. }
14... e5
{ Before bothering the knight on a4, Black fights for the dark squares and would like to recapture with the knight. That's why White's earlier @@StartFEN@@2bq1rk1/r3nppp/p1npp3/8/Np2PP2/1N1B4/PPP1Q1PP/2KR3R w - - 0 14@@EndFEN@@  14.Qe3  @@StartBracket@@covered in the next trainable@@EndBracket@@ is stronger  as Black's knight on c6 is constrained to guard the rook on a7, thus ...e5 is unplayable. }
15. f5 Bd7 { Black resumes the idea. } 16. Qd2
{ White improves his attacking odds and indirectly defends the knight. } 16...
Nc8 17. g4 Qe8 { What a way to improve the threat. } 18. f6 Nd8 19. fxg7 Kxg7
{ White has nothing more than a perpetual check. } *

