12. h4
{ White could try to be smart and start the kingside attack without defining the placement of the king. }
12... d6
{ Black can also be quite flexible and wait until White castles long. The ...b4 threat is always in the air. }
13. h5 h6 14. g4 f6 15. f4 Nd7
{ Black's defensive capabilities are not worse. Now Black is thinking about pushing ...e5 to control all the dark squares on the kingside, effectively stopping the attack.   Here's how the game could continue if White proceeds with his plan:  16.g5  fxg5  17.fxg5  hxg5  .  As soon as White pushes h6, Black can play ...g6 and hide the king on the h-file.  18.Qxg5  Ne5  19.O-O-O  N7c6  Black's defense looks rock solid, while his attacking chances on the queenside might still be there. }
