7. Nc2
{ If White retreats with the knight on c2 early, this gives Black freedom with the choice of plans. Try to play something dynamic. }
7... b6 8. Be2
{ Positioning the bishop on e2 forces White to continue with f3 and even further weaken the dark squares on the kingside. }
8... Bb7 9. f3 Bd6
{ This is a very common idea of the Sicilian Kan and another reason why we don't want to play the passive Hedgehog. With the white knight gone from the center, Black no longer needs to watch out from the typical Nb5 trick. }
10. g3 h5
{ This maneuver you will see quite a lot! Black's threat is to push ...h4 and create some big targets on the kingside. }
