10. O-O g6
{ Not only Black does give the dark-squared bishop a new role on the long h8-a1 diagonal, but this move also deals with White's immediate f5 push. }
11. f5 { With the black pawn on g6 Black suddenly has an unexpected resource. }
11... gxf5 12. exf5 Rg8 13. Ne1 Nbd7
{ Unexpectedly, Black starts an attack on the kingside and will simply castle long. }
14. fxe6 fxe6 15. Qe2 O-O-O
{ Black's initiative certainly looks more real than what White is planning to do on the queenside in the distant future. }
