{ Here's the thing - White can't ignore the pressure on the h2-pawn forever. Where is his king going to castle? Black can slowly prepare the ...d5 push with moves like ...Be5 and ...Rfd8.   14...Bxh2??  don't mistake this with one of the previous lines - there's a major difference.  15.Rxh2  Qxh2  16.Bf4  Qh4  17.g3  the Black rook on b8 is simply undefended. }
