{ A reasonable choice, keeping some degree of control of the dark squares. Black here has many interesting ideas - pushing forward the h-pawn, or castling with shoving the f5 push, or once again, fighting for the control of the dark squares. }
14... Bc5 15. Qd2 a5
{ One of the core ideas of the variation and probably the simplest choice of them all. }
16. Bf4 e5 17. Bg5 Qd8
{ Black's game is straightforward - fight for the dark squares and keep White with his light-squared bishop, preferably against a knight. }
