{ White squeezed out of the position every single trick there is but it's still not enough to claim something real. }
10... O-O 11. O-O-O
{ Otherwise, the alternative is  11.c5  and it allows Black to trade the dark-squared bishops via f4-square and then push ...e5. The weakness of the b6-square is not enough for advantage. }
11... Be7 12. f4 b5 { Black's counterplay on the queenside is quite real. } *

[Event "?"]
