{ 9.Bg5?!  While this maneuver is one of the main ideas, including  9.O-O  and  9...Nc6  , here it's too early. @@StartFEN@@rnb2rk1/1pqp1ppp/p3pn2/6B1/1bPNP3/2NQ4/PP2BPPP/R3K2R b KQ - 8 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Qe5  Because White has not castled short, the pawn on e4 now is under attack.  10.Bxf6  If White has to commit to this trade, that's a clear concession.  10...Qxf6  11.O-O  Nc6  12.Rad1  The position is equal but White has excellent chances to get a worse position as Black's dark-squared bishop eventually will become even stronger. }
