14. Rac1 Bd7 15. b3 Rac8
{ Black is looking for ways to create counterplay on the queenside with ...b5. }
16. Kh1 { This could be another quiet way to prepare the kingside attack. }
16... h6 17. Bd2
{ Here the bishop stops Black's ...Qa5 maneuver. It seems more natural to play  17.Be3  but then Black proceeds with the ...Qa5 and ...b5 plan. }
17... b5 18. cxb5 Qb6
{ If White plays Qe3 to protect the knight, there's ...Ng4, both work - the position is balanced. Keep in the mind following trick! }
19. Be3 Rxc3 20. Rxc3 Nxe4 { Black wins material. } *

