{ White tries to be very creative and launch a kingside assault while still keeping the king in the center. What should Black do? }
13... b5
{ Activity above all! Black is ready to meet White's g5 with b4 - one of the most typical Sicilian counterstrikes. }
14. cxb5 Nxd4 15. Bxd4 d5
{ There comes another counterstrike - Black rips White's center apart. Black is very dynamic and it should be quite obvious that White's approach with g4 can seriously backfire as the White king will never be safe. }
16. b6 { This is the most forcing move. } 16... Rxb6 17. Bxb6 Qxb6 18. exd5 Bb7
{ The White king is wide open - White will have to carefully navigate through a minefield. }
